        <abstract> 
<p>Replies to Francis Galton’s paper on tranfusing blood between rabbits to test Pangenesis [<hi rend="italic">Proc. R. Soc. Lond.</hi> 19 (1871): 393–40]. FG’s conclusion that his experiments prove Pangenesis to be false is "a little hasty", since CD had never maintained that gemmules in the blood formed any part of his hypothesis.</p> 
        </abstract>
